d%20they're%20attacking%20union%20jobs%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20at%20an%20October%20rally%20in%20Reading%2C%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImmigrants%20account%20for%20a%20third%20of%20workers%20in%20jobs%20paying%20under%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20the%20conservative%20think%20tank%20American%20Compass%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericancompass.org%2Fa-guide-to-labor-supply%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Duncan%20Braid%2C%20its%20coalition%20director%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20competition%20from%20those%20immigrants%20hurts%20lower-income%20Americans.%20He%20said%20while%20mass%20deportations%20may%20cost%20the%20government%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20its%20role%20is%20to%20protect%20the%20Constitution%20and%20its%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20currently%20have%20a%20situation%20where%20there%20is%20sort%20of%20an%20unlimited%20number%20of%20lower-skilled%20people%20coming%20into%20this%20country%2C%20and%20them%20competing%20directly%20with%20other%20low-skilled%20Americans%20already%20here%20would%20necessarily%2C%20just%20based%20on%20very%20basic%20theory%2C%20suppress%20their%20wages%2C%26quot%3B%20Braid%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20research%20suggests%20the%20opposite.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32389%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20paper%20by%20economists%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Davis%2C%20found%20that%20increases%20in%20immigration%20can%20boost%20native%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20don't%20see%20much%20evidence%20of%20substitution%20between%20unauthorized%20immigrants%20and%20US-born%20people%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fpeople%2Fchloe-east%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChloe%20East%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20partly%20because%20the%20jobs%20that%20unauthorized%20immigrants%20are%20willing%20to%20take%20are%20lower-paying%2C%20are%20more%20dangerous%2C%20and%20are%20less%20desirable%20for%20other%20reasons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FrweTK%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Top%205%20occupations%20as%20a%20share%20of%20unauthorized%20immigrant%20workers%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22547%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd881018-1654-4a0f-89bc-4814c3eb733e%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20a%20mass%20deportation%20would%20cost%20the%20government%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20campaign%20has%20talked%20little%20about%20how%20mass%20deportations%20could%20be%20implemented%20and%20on%20what%20scale.%20While%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Trump%20carried%20out%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.migrationpolicy.org%2Farticle%2Fbiden-deportation-record%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.5%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20deportations%20and%20made%20similar%20promises%20about%20mass%20deportation%20but%20was%20met%20with%20various%20legal%20challenges.%20At%20a%20campaign%20rally%20on%20October%2011%20in%20Aurora%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Trump%20pledged%20to%20use%20a%201798%20law%20to%20deport%20suspected%20members%20of%20cartels%20and%20gangs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20carry%20out%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bthe%20largest%20domestic%20deportation%20operation%20in%20American%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20plans%20to%20bolster%20ICE%20raids%20by%20reassigning%20federal%20agents%20and%20recruiting%20from%20local%20police%20forces%20and%20says%20he'll%20order%20the%20construction%20of%20new%20detention%20camps%20for%20people%20waiting%20for%20their%20cases%20to%20be%20processed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F11%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-2025-immigration-agenda.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20be%20an%20expensive%20undertaking.%20Using%20Census%20Bureau%20data%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanimmigrationcouncil.org%2Fresearch%2Fmass-deportation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Immigration%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20it%20would%20cost%20the%20federal%20government%20over%20%24315%20billion%2C%20including%20hiring%20up%20to%20409%2C000%20new%20government%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFo1VX%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20much%20a%20mass%20deportation%20could%20cost%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22431%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20labor%20market%20disruptions%2C%20economists%20also%20say%20the%20country%20would%20lose%20tax%20revenue.%20Unauthorized%20immigrants%20paid%20%2496.7%20billion%20in%20federal%2C%20state%2C%20and%20local%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%248%2C889%20per%20person%20%E2%80%94%20in%202022%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fitep.org%2Fundocumented-immigrants-taxes-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstitute%20on%20Taxation%20and%20Economic%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%20In%202022%2C%20unauthorized%20immigrants%20paid%20about%20%24704%20million%20in%20state%20and%20local%20taxes%20in%20Arizona%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupporters%20of%20deportation%20argue%20that%20the%20loss%20of%20tax%20revenue%20would%20be%20offset%20by%20savings%20on%20reduced%20services%20for%20immigrants.%20A%20study%20from%20the%20conservative%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmanhattan.institute%2Farticle%2Fthe-lifetime-fiscal-impact-of-immigrants%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManhattan%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20while%20older%20and%20less-educated%20immigrants%2C%20on%20average%2C%20receive%20more%20in%20federal%20benefits%20than%20they%20pay%20in%20taxes%2C%20higher-educated%20young%20immigrants%20are%20taxed%20more%20than%20they%20get%20back%20over%20their%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20campaign%20has%20made%20a%20similar%20argument%2C%20saying%20that%20welfare%20programs%2C%20taxpayer-subsidized%20health%20insurance%2C%20transportation%20costs%20through%20FEMA%2C%20and%20education%20expenses%20for%20immigrants%20ultimately%20cost%20taxpayers%20billions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20real%20economic%20crisis%20is%20the%20%24182%20billion%20American%20tax%20dollars%20spent%20each%20year%20to%20cover%20the%20costs%20of%2020%20million%20illegal%20immigrants%20that%20have%20flooded%20our%20communities%20thanks%20to%20Kamala%20Harris'%20wide-open%20border%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20Rogers%2C%20an%20RNC%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump's%20mass%20deportation%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20will%20not%20only%20make%20our%20communities%20safer%20but%20will%20save%20Americans%20from%20footing%20the%20bill%20for%20years%20to%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20Rogers%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22636206ff-627e-4eb3-9f7e-3ba104a3e936%5C%22%3EEconomic%20growth%20and%20inflation%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMass%20deportations%20could%20have%20consequences%20for%20economic%20growth%20as%20a%20whole.%20The%20Trump%20campaign%20hasn't%20addressed%20overall%20growth%20and%20inflation%20concerns%20but%20has%20said%20deportations%20would%20help%20reduce%20demand%20in%20the%20housing%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20more%20macro%20scale%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piie.com%2Fblogs%2Frealtime-economics%2F2024%2Fmass-deportations-would-harm-us-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeterson%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20International%20Economics%20said%20gross%20domestic%20product%20could%20fall%201.2%25%20below%20baseline%20by%202028%20if%201.3%20million%20people%20are%20deported%2C%20while%20inflation%20could%20climb%200.5%20percentage%20points%20above%20current%20estimates%20by%202026.%20In%20a%20more%20extreme%20scenario%20where%208.4%20million%20people%20are%20deported%2C%20GDP%20could%20fall%20by%207.4%25%20and%20inflation%20could%20climb%203.5%20percentage%20points%20above%20baseline%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Immigration%20Council%20has%20a%20similarly%20negative%20view%20of%20the%20economic%20impact.%20It%20estimated%20that%20the%20US%20could%20lose%20between%204.2%25%20and%206.8%25%20in%20GDP%20if%20about%2011%20million%20people%20are%20deported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20very%20easy%20for%20an%20average%20American%20to%20see%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20policy%20in%20their%20daily%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Marcus%20Noland%2C%20the%20executive%20vice%20president%20and%20director%20of%20studies%20at%20the%20Peterson%20Institute%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-harris-immigration-jobs-arizona-economy-mass-deportation-employment-wages-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730300176000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671691dfa0a0cc14f222a75a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-harris-immigration-jobs-arizona-economy-mass-deportation-employment-wages-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mass%20deportations%20former%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20proposing%20could%20reshape%20labor%20markets%2C%20strain%20services%2C%20and%20impact%20economic%20growth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-harris-immigration-jobs-arizona-economy-mass-deportation-employment-wages-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IPL%20retentions%3A%20No%20Pant%20as%20DC%20finalise%20their%20list%20of%20players%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730300137000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114783918%2Cimgsize-28024.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fipl%2Ftop-stories%2Fipl-retentions-no-rishabh-pant-as-delhi-capitals-finalise-their-list-of-players%2Farticleshow%2F114783952.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wicketkeeper-batter%20Rishabh%20Pant%20will%20not%20be%20part%20of%20Delhi%20Capitals%20from%20IPL%202025%2C%20as%20the%20team%20has%20decided%20not%20to%20retain%20him.%20They%20will%20look%20for%20new%20captaincy%20options%2C%20potentially%20exploring%20choices%20in%20the%20mega%20auction.%20Axar%20Patel%20is%20a%20possible%20option%2C%20but%20Shreyas%20Iyer%20might%20also%20be%20on%20their%20radar%20due%20to%20his%20past%20success%20with%20the%20team.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22SAHIL%20MALHOTRA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fipl%2Ftop-stories%2Fipl-retentions-no-rishabh-pant-as-delhi-capitals-finalise-their-list-of-players%2Farticleshow%2F114783952.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Devanahalli%E2%80%99s%20Water%20Solutions%20Could%20Be%20the%20Key%20to%20Bengaluru%E2%80%99s%20Water%20Shortage%20Problem%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F302015%2Fboson-whitewater-bengaluru-startup-converts-stp-water-to-high-quality-potable-drinking-water%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoson%20Whitewater%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20water%20utility%20venture%20that%20converts%20treated%20water%20from%20sewage%20treatment%20plants%20(STPs)%20into%20high-quality%20potable%20water%20%E2%80%94%20has%20partnered%20with%20the%20non-profit%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F173853%2Fbengaluru-ground-water-crisis-well-digging-day-zero-zenrainman%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiome%20Environmental%20Trust%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20launch%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20indirect%20potable%20water%20reuse%20project.%20This%20innovative%20initiative%2C%20located%20in%20Devanahalli%2C%2040%20kilometres%20northeast%20of%20Bengaluru%2C%20uses%20managed%20aquifer%20recharge%20to%20achieve%20sustainable%20water%20reuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20participants%20%5Bof%20this%20project%5D%2C%20the%20project%20produces%206.4%20lakh%20litres%20of%20potable%20drinking%20water%20per%20day%2C%20adhering%20to%20BIS%20(Bureau%20of%20Indian%20Standards)-10500%20standards.%20The%20clean%20water%20directly%20benefits%20thousands%20of%20residents%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F139499%2Fdevanahalli-toilets-karnataka-odf-fstp-swachh-bharat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDevanahalli%20%3C%2Fa%3Emunicipality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20does%20this%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%222400846096%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimply%20put%2C%20treated%20wastewater%20from%20a%20sewage%20treatment%20plant%20is%20first%20pumped%20into%20Bagalur%20Lake%2C%20where%20it%20is%20diluted%20with%20rainwater.%20This%20water%20is%20then%20directed%20to%20Devanahalli%E2%80%99s%20Sihineeru%20Kere%20Lake%20through%20a%20pipeline%2C%20further%20diluted%20with%20rainwater%2C%20and%20subsequently%20filtered%20through%20the%20earth%20to%20recharge%20the%20aquifer.%20The%20water%20is%20then%20picked%20up%20from%20the%20aquifer%20through%20a%20dug%20well%20and%20shallow%20filter%20borewells%2C%20treated%2C%20and%20then%20supplied%20to%20the%20town%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20this%20an%20indirect%20potable%20water%20reuse%20project%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20project%20uses%20an%20environmental%20buffer%20like%20a%20lake%20for%20dilution%20with%20rainwater%20and%2For%20a%20groundwater%20aquifer%20for%20earth%20filtration.%20This%20water%20eventually%20goes%20through%20a%20final%20treatment%20stage%20before%20it%20is%20supplied%20to%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229253875046%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20the%20project%20is%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20effort%20to%20rejuvenate%2065%20lakes%20in%20Bengaluru%20employing%20treated%20wastewater%20and%20rainwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20project%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20involves%20reviving%20an%20old%20well%20and%20digging%20borewells%20to%20access%20the%20aquifer%2C%20along%20with%20the%20installation%20of%20water%20treatment%20plants%20in%20two%20phases.%20Now%2C%20the%20system%20provides%206.4%20lakh%20litres%20of%20water%20daily%2C%20helping%20supplement%20the%20domestic%20water%20requirement%20of%2045%2C000%20residents%20in%20Devanahalli.%20This%20was%20made%20possible%20through%20the%20collaboration%20of%20many%20organisations%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Carl%20Zeiss%2C%20Rotary%20South%20Parade%20Bangalore%2C%20and%20Wipro%20Foundation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201000px)%20100vw%2C%201000px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWater-Reuse-Project-Lake-Image-1730296908.jpg%3Ffit%3D1200%252C628%26quality%3D89%26ssl%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bengaluru%20water%20crisis%20and%20lake%20rejuvenation%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWater-Reuse-Project-Lake-Image-1730296908.jpg%3Fw%3D1200%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWater-Reuse-Project-Lake-Image-1730296908.jpg%3Fresize%3D300%252C157%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWater-Reuse-Project-Lake-Image-1730296908.jpg%3Fresize%3D500%252C262%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWater-Reuse-Project-Lake-Image-1730296908.jpg%3Fresize%3D768%252C402%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWater-Reuse-Project-Lake-Image-1730296908.jpg%3Fresize%3D150%252C79%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-373549%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20project%20is%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20effort%20to%20rejuvenate%2065%20lakes%20in%20Bengaluru%20employing%20treated%20wastewater%20and%20rainwater%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20further%2C%20it%20claims%20that%20the%20project%20is%20energy-efficient%2C%20using%20just%200.25%20units%20of%20electricity%20per%201%2C000%20litres%2C%20and%20follows%20the%20Union%20Government%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmohua.gov.in%2Fupload%2Fuploadfiles%2Ffiles%2FAMRUT-Operational-Guidelines.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMRUT%202.0%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20thus%20serving%20as%20a%20model%20for%20future%20urban%20water%20management.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20Union%20Government%20launched%20the%20AMRUT%202.0%20scheme%20to%20%E2%80%9Caugment%20infrastructure%20for%20water%20supply%2C%20sewerage%20and%20septage%20management%20and%20rejuvenate%20the%20water%20bodies%20aiming%20to%20improve%20the%20quality%20of%20life%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%227521127830%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Vikas%20Brahmavar%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Boson%20Whitewater%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20AMRUT%202.0%2C%20there%20are%20specific%20guidelines%20on%20making%20the%20project%20commercially%20viable%20and%20ensuring%20water%20quality%2C%20which%20means%20we%E2%80%99ve%20taken%20careful%20steps%20to%20maintain%20high%20water%20standards%20and%20an%20appropriate%20design.%20In%20terms%20of%20power%20usage%2C%20we%20cannot%20have%20a%20complex%2C%20elaborate%20treatment%20system%20that%20consumes%20a%20lot%20of%20power%20for%20water%20treatment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20only%20use%20a%20few%20pumps%20to%20move%20water%20through%20the%20system%2C%20keeping%20power%20consumption%20low.%20Now%2C%20imagine%20if%20we%20had%20to%20use%20RO%20(reverse%20osmosis)%20and%20UF%20(ultrafiltration)%3B%20it%20would%20become%20too%20complex%20in%20terms%20of%20power%20requirements.%20Since%20the%20water%20from%20the%20well%20and%20the%20shallow%20aquifer%20meets%20IS%2010500%20standards%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20able%20to%20treat%20it%20with%20a%20simple%20four-stage%20treatment%20process%20to%20ensure%20safety%2C%20making%20it%20suitable%20for%20domestic%20supply%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVishwanath%20S%2C%20a%20civil%20engineer%2C%20water%20management%20expert%20and%20advisor%20at%20Biome%20Environmental%20Trust%2C%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CDevanahalli%20town%20relies%20heavily%20on%20deep%20borewells%20for%20its%20water%20supply.%20Through%20this%20project%2C%20we%20aim%20to%20revive%20the%20local%20lake%2C%20recharge%20groundwater%2C%20and%20explore%20how%20a%20town%20can%20become%20self-sufficient%20by%20using%20both%20local%20water%20sources%20and%20treated%20wastewater.%20The%20project%20has%20the%20capacity%20to%20meet%20Devanahalli%E2%80%99s%205.4%20MLD%20(million%20litres%20per%20day)%20water%20demand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5B1%20MLD%20(million%20litres%20per%20day)%20is%20equal%20to%201%2C000%20KLD%20(thousand%20litres%20per%20day)%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201000px)%20100vw%2C%201000px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Ffit%3D1600%252C719%26quality%3D89%26ssl%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bengaluru%20water%20shortage%20can%20be%20addressed%20by%20wastewater%20treatment%20and%20lake%20rejuvenation%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fw%3D1600%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fresize%3D300%252C135%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fresize%3D500%252C225%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fresize%3D768%252C345%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fresize%3D1536%252C690%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fresize%3D1200%252C539%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0019-1730297076.jpg%3Fresize%3D150%252C67%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-373557%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWastewater%20treatment%20is%20the%20key%20to%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20conserve%20Bengaluru%E2%80%99s%20water%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Phase%201%2C%20a%20water%20treatment%20plant%20was%20installed%20to%20provide%20240%20kilo%20litres%20(2.4%20lakh%20litres)%20of%20water%20daily.%20In%20Phase%202%2C%20the%20project%20expanded%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20four%20more%20filter%20borewells%2C%20a%20reconstructed%2060%20kilolitres%20(KL)%20sump%2C%20and%20a%20new%20400%20KLD%20water%20treatment%20plant.%20The%20system%20now%20delivers%20640%20KL%20(6.4%20lakh)%20of%20water%20daily%2C%20benefiting%20the%20Devanahalli%20residents%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVikas%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20vision%20is%20to%20create%20a%20sustainable%20third%20source%20of%20water%20by%20utilising%20every%20drop%20of%20wastewater%20generated%20in%20our%20cities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20break%20down%20the%20project%20into%20its%20finer%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20did%20we%20get%20here%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Biome%20has%20been%20doing%20is%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%20old%20well%20near%20the%20Sihineeru%20Kere%20lake%2C%20estimated%20to%20be%20over%20100%20years%20old.%20Due%20to%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20dryness%20and%20lack%20of%20water%20seepage%20into%20the%20well%2C%20people%20started%20using%20it%20to%20dispose%20of%20debris.%20Biome%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20local%20%3Cem%3Epanchayat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20cleaned%20out%20this%20well%20in%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20well%20was%20cleaned%20and%20treated%20wastewater%20was%20directed%20to%20the%20lake%2C%20the%20well%2C%20situated%20about%2025%20to%2030%20feet%20from%20the%20lake%2C%20began%20to%20fill%20as%20water%20seeped%20through%20the%20earth%20from%20the%20lake.%20This%20natural%20earth%20filtration%20helped%20fill%20the%20well.%20Biome%20then%20tested%20this%20well%20water%2C%20which%20met%20the%20IS%2010500%20standards.%20Over%20time%2C%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20(IISc)%20got%20involved%2C%20recognising%20the%20water%20quality%20and%20exploring%20how%20to%20make%20it%20usable%20for%20the%20public.%20Since%20the%20well%20water%20filtered%20through%20the%20earth%2C%20it%20was%20deemed%20safe%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Vikas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20a%20two-phase%20project%20was%20initiated.%20The%20first%20phase%2C%20completed%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20ago%2C%20was%20designed%20to%20recover%20200%20KL%20(2%20lakh%20litres)%20of%20water%20daily.%20Water%20from%20the%20well%20was%20processed%20through%20disk%20filtration%2C%20activated%20carbon%20filtration%20(with%20high%20iodine%20value)%2C%20UV%20(ultraviolet%20light%20disinfection)%20treatment%2C%20and%20basic%20chlorine%20disinfection%20before%20being%20sent%20to%20a%20sump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201000px)%20100vw%2C%201000px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Ffit%3D1599%252C720%26quality%3D89%26ssl%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221599%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bengaluru%20water%20shortage%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20with%20lake%20rejuvenation%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fw%3D1599%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201599w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fresize%3D300%252C135%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fresize%3D500%252C225%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fresize%3D768%252C346%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fresize%3D1536%252C692%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fresize%3D1200%252C540%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0018-1730297279.jpg%3Fresize%3D150%252C68%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-373571%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESolutions%20to%20Bengaluru%E2%80%99s%20water%20shortage%3A%20Lake%20rejuvenation%20by%20employing%20treated%20wastewater%20is%20a%20core%20component%20of%20this%20model%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20sump%20also%20received%20deep%20borewell%20water.%20In%20that%20area%2C%20deep%20borewells%2C%20which%20reach%20depths%20of%20around%201%2C000%20to%201%2C100%20feet%2C%20often%20contain%20fluoride%20and%20other%20contaminants%2C%20making%20the%20water%20usable%20only%20for%20bathing%20and%20similar%20purposes.%20Water%20from%20the%20sump%20was%20pumped%20to%20the%20entire%20Devanahalli%20town%2C%20which%20requires%20about%205.4%20to%206%20MLD%20of%20water%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBiome%20envisioned%20that%20by%20meeting%20just%2010%25%20of%20the%20town%E2%80%99s%20water%20needs%2C%20they%20could%20demonstrate%20a%20viable%20model%20for%20small%20towns%20across%20India.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20where%20lakes%20and%20wastewater%20are%20available%2C%20communities%20could%20effectively%20use%20such%20resources%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Vikas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhase%201%20was%20installed%20in%20July-August%202023%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20year%20of%20testing.%20Once%20it%20proved%20effective%2C%20Phase%202%20was%20launched%20in%20August%202024.%20Now%2C%20both%20phases%20are%20operational%2C%20supplying%20600%20KL%20or%206%20lakh%20litres%20of%20water%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20next%20phase%2C%20we%20are%20planning%20to%20replicate%20this%20process%20at%20Doddakere%20Lake%2C%20a%20large%20lake%20with%20multiple%20unused%20wells%20currently%20filled%20with%20debris%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20the%20flow%20of%20water%20from%20lake%20to%20lake%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWater%20is%20treated%20at%20the%20government-operated%20STP%20called%20Hebbal%20Nagawara%20Treatment%20Plant%20(HN%20Valley%20Treatment%20Plant).%20From%20this%20plant%2C%20it%20is%20pumped%20to%20Bagalur%20Lake%20through%20a%20pipeline%20and%20then%20from%20that%20lake%20it%20comes%20to%20Sihi%20Neerukere%20Lake.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20specific%20reason%20they%20do%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20lakes%20often%20dry%20up%2C%20and%20the%20only%20way%20to%20refill%20them%20is%20by%20pumping%20treated%20wastewater.%20Government-run%20STPs%20are%20required%20to%20meet%20certain%20qualities%20so%20that%20the%20wastewater%20they%20treat%20can%20be%20pumped%20into%20the%20lakes.%20Only%20if%20that%20quality%20is%20met%2C%20the%20treated%20wastewater%20is%20sent%20to%20the%20lake%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vikas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20why%20does%20treated%20wastewater%20require%20further%20dilution%20by%20rainwater%20in%20both%20Bagalur%20Lake%20and%20Sihi%20Neerukere%20Lake%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhenever%20the%20treated%20water%20goes%20to%20the%20lake%2C%20during%20the%20rainy%20season%20there%20is%20always%20dilution%20from%20the%20rain%2C%20and%20Bengaluru%20probably%20gets%2047%20or%2060%20days%20of%20rain%20across%20various%20months.%20So%2C%20based%20on%20this%20rain%2C%20there%20is%20always%20dilution%20in%20the%20lake.%20So%2C%20we%20do%20not%20purposefully%20do%20it%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20of%20giving%20it%20to%20the%20lake%20is%20to%20dilute%20it%20with%20natural%20water%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20explained%20earlier%2C%20treated%20wastewater%20that%20is%20further%20diluted%20with%20rainwater%20is%20diverted%20to%20Devanahalli%E2%80%99s%20Sihi%20Neerukere%20Lake.%20Here%2C%20it%20is%20further%20diluted%20with%20rainwater%2C%20and%20subsequently%20filtered%20through%20the%20earth%20to%20recharge%20the%20aquifer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Sihi%20Neerukere%20Lake%20will%20dry%20up%20if%20no%20water%20flows%20into%20it.%20Devanahalli%20always%20had%20problems%20with%20drought.%20Back%20in%202015-16%2C%20this%20lake%20almost%20went%20dry.%20The%20local%20governing%20body%20asked%20the%20Government%20to%20send%20the%20treated%20wastewater%20to%20the%20lake%20because%20it%20would%20go%20defunct.%20That%20was%20the%20initial%20purpose%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20this%20treated%20wastewater%20is%20once%20again%20further%20diluted%20with%20rainwater%2C%20it%20is%20subsequently%20filtered%20through%20the%20earth%20to%20recharge%20the%20aquifer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Phase%202%2C%20they%20used%20something%20called%20a%20shallow%20aquifer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20instead%20of%20digging%20a%20borewell%20at%201%2C000%20feet%2C%20you%20dig%20a%20filter%20borewell%20(shallow%20aquifer)%20at%20a%20maximum%20depth%20of%2050%20to%2090%20feet.%20Here%2C%20well%20water%20seeps%20again%20through%20natural%20filtration%20and%20enters%20the%20filter%20borewell.%20Filter%20borewells%20are%20essentially%20shallow%20borewells%20with%20pores%20in%20the%20pipe%20for%20filtering%2C%20and%20the%20plan%20was%20for%20about%20six%20or%20seven%20filter%20borewells%2C%20I%20believe%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Vikas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWater%20then%20undergoes%20another%20level%20of%20earth%20filtration%20before%20reaching%20another%20sump%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201000px)%20100vw%2C%201000px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0020-1730297386.jpg%3Ffit%3D1600%252C719%26quality%3D89%26ssl%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0020-1730297386.jpg%3Fw%3D1600%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FIMG-20241030-WA0020-1730297386.jpg%3Fresize%3D300%252C135%26amp%3Bquality%3D89%26amp%3Bssl%3D1%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fi0.wp.com%2Fen-media.theb