%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcy0lpdl2lweo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20To%20Play%20Or%20Not%20To%20Play%3A%20Is%20It%20The%20End%20Of%20The%20Line%20For%20Novak%20Djokovic%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F650omvh_novak_625x300_30_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20live%20and%20breathe%20sport%2C%20or%20follow%20it%20closely%2C%20it's%20a%20microcosm%20of%20life%20itself.%20Every%20single%20emotion%20that%20a%20human%20being%20is%20capable%20of%20experiencing%20can%20be%20found%20on%20a%20football%20pitch%2C%20or%20a%20tennis%20court%2C%20or%20a%20boxing%20ring%2C%20or%20a%20cricket%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20when%20a%20titan%20of%20sport%20approaches%20the%20end%20of%20her%20or%20his%20career%2C%20this%20gamut%20of%20emotions%20and%20experiences%20is%20revealed%20when%20one%20dissects%20the%20journey%20and%20the%20road%20travelled.%20As%20things%20stand%20right%20now%2C%20Novak%20Djokovic%2C%20a%20modern-day%20great%2C%20may%20be%20at%20the%20threshold%20of%20bringing%20the%20curtain%20down%20on%20what%20has%20been%20a%20phenomenal%2C%20history-making%20career.%20But%20he%20would%20ideally%20like%20to%20continue%20playing%20and%20being%20competitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20why%20are%20we%20talking%20about%20this%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20the%20year%202024%20was%20the%20first%20since%202017%20when%20Djokovic%20didn't%20win%20a%20single%20Grand%20Slam%20title%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20he%20is%2037%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20he%20has%20really%20done%20it%20all%E2%80%94won%20the%20most%20singles%20Slam%20titles%20ever%20for%20a%20male%20player%20(24)%20and%20now%20also%20an%20Olympic%20gold%20(which%20he%20called%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20greatest%20success%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20career)%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20men's%20singles%20players%20are%20well%20and%20truly%20pushing%20him%2C%20challenging%20him%20at%20every%20step%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20he%20doesn't%20have%20much%20left%20in%20the%20tank%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20honest%20answer%20is%20that%20it%20can%20be%20any%20one%20of%20these%20reasons%2C%20or%20all%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Last%20Competitive%20Year%20For%20Djokovic%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20emotional%20tennis%20fan%20in%20us%20would%20of%20course%20want%20Djokovic%20to%20continue%20playing%20for%20as%20long%20as%20he%20truly%20wants.%20After%20all%2C%20this%20man%20has%20managed%20to%20do%20what%20at%20one%20time%20was%20absolutely%20unthinkable.%20When%20Pete%20Sampras%20got%20to%2014%20Grand%20Slam%20titles%2C%20the%20world%20was%20in%20awe%20of%20the%20achievement.%20Federer%20and%20Nadal%20bettered%20that%20tally%20and%20Djokovic%20has%20as%20many%20as%20ten%20Slam%20titles%20more%20than%20Sampras%2C%20four%20more%20than%20Federer%20and%20two%20more%20than%20Nadal%2C%20currently.%20Then%2C%20there%20are%20those%20who%20would%20want%20to%20see%20him%20wave%20goodbye%20on%20a%20high%20and%20not%20struggle%20to%20compete%E2%80%94something%20that%20we%20saw%20Rafa%20go%20through%20over%20the%20last%20year%20or%20so%2C%20which%20was%20honestly%20painful%20to%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20are%20we%20heading%20into%20a%20year%20that%20could%20be%20the%20last%20competitive%20one%20in%20Novak%20Djokovic's%20career%3F%20Maybe.%20Many%2C%20of%20course%2C%20might%20want%20to%20take%20that%20with%20a%20pinch%20of%20salt.%20Retire%20in%202025%3F%20Really%3F%3Cbr%3E%5CnHowever%2C%20there%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20conversation%20now%20has%20changed%20from%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20he%20announce%3F%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20will%20he%20announce%3F%E2%80%9D.%20And%20that%2C%20as%20always%2C%20rests%20entirely%20with%20the%20individual.%20Don't%20be%20surprised%20if%20it%20does%20happen%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20million-dollar%20question%20here%20is%2C%20can%20Djokovic%20realistically%20win%20more%20Slams%3F%20Remember%2C%20in%202024%2C%20Jannik%20Sinner%20and%20Carlos%20Alcaraz%2C%20two%20of%20the%20biggest%20flag-bearers%20of%20the%20new%20generation%20of%20men's%20tennis%20players%2C%20split%20the%20four%20Slams%20equally%20between%20the%20two%20of%20them.%20They%20are%20doing%20to%20Djokovic%20what%20he%20did%20to%20Federer%20and%20Nadal%20at%20one%20time.%20The%20aura%20of%20invincibility%20has%20no%20doubt%20been%20severely%20dented.%20The%20competition%20is%20very%20real%20and%20the%20old%20warrior%20is%20feeling%20the%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Maybe%20I'll%20Change%20My%20Mind'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20true%20that%20Djokovic%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20go%20out%20on%20a%20huge%20high%2C%20when%20he%20won%20the%20one%20accolade%20that%20was%20missing%20from%20his%20trophy%20cabinet%3A%20the%20Olympic%20singles%20gold%2C%20an%20achievement%20that%20saw%20him%20clinch%20a%20career%20Golden%20Slam.%20The%20most%20successful%20male%20tennis%20player%20of%20all%20time%20and%20the%20joint%20most%20successful%20overall%20(pre-%20and%20post-open%20era)%20knows%20that%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Argentine%20publication%3Cem%3E%20La%20Nacion%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CSome%20people%20think%20I%20should%20leave%20tennis%20on%20a%20high%3A%20%E2%80%98You%20won%20gold%2C%20you%20won%20everything%2C%20say%20goodbye'%E2%80%A6%20Some%20people%20think%20I%20should%20keep%20going%20as%20long%20as%20I%20still%20think%20I%20can%20be%20the%20favourite%20for%20a%20Grand%20Slam.%20I%20think%20more%20like%20them.%E2%80%9D%20But%20then%20he%20also%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CMaybe%20I%20will%20change%20my%20mind.%20I%20don't%20know.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2023%20Wasn't%20All%20That%20Bad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20defence%2C%202023%20was%20a%20very%20good%20year%20for%20him.%20He%20won%20three%20of%20the%20four%20Slams%20that%20year%20(Australian%20Open%2C%20French%20Open%20and%20US%20Open)%20and%20finished%20as%20the%20number%20one%20player%20in%20the%20ATP%20rankings%E2%80%94the%20eighth%20time%20overall%20that%20he%20was%20the%20year-end%20number%20one%2C%20the%20most%20for%20any%20male%20tennis%20player.%20That%20is%20a%20telling%20statistic.%20So%2C%20it's%20quite%20plausible%20that%20despite%20not%20winning%20a%20single%20title%20in%202024%20(at%20the%20time%20of%20writing%20this%20article)%2C%20barring%20the%20Olympic%20gold%2C%20Djokovic%20thought%20that%20he%20could%20still%20dig%20deep%20and%20find%20the%20incredible%20gumption%20that%20has%20been%20his%20biggest%20weapon%20throughout%20his%20stellar%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20he%20must%20have%20felt%20that%20something%20was%20off%20this%20year.%20He%20made%20only%20one%20Slam%20final%20this%20year%2C%20which%20was%20at%20SW19%2C%20and%20was%20well%20and%20truly%20humbled%20by%20Alcaraz%20in%20straight%20sets.%20He%20was%20out%20of%20the%20French%20Open%20in%20the%20quarters%2C%20out%20of%20the%20Australian%20Open%20in%20the%20semis%2C%20and%20couldn't%20go%20beyond%20the%20third%20round%20at%20the%20US%20Open.%20His%20win-loss%20record%20(as%20of%20October%2029%2C%202024)%20for%20the%20year%20stands%20at%2037-46.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20is%20he%20feeling%E2%80%94physically%20and%20mentally%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDjokovic%20Can't%20%3Cem%3EJust%20%3C%2Fem%3ECompete%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20every%20athlete's%20life%2C%20there%20comes%20a%20time%20when%20they%20realise%20that%20they%20just%20can't%20perform%20at%20the%20level%20they%20would%20like.%20That%20is%20always%20the%20last%20straw.%20No%20athlete%2C%20especially%20the%20greats%2C%20wants%20to%20%3Cem%3Ejust%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecompete.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIs%20Djokovic%20slowing%20down%3F%20Can%20he%20feel%20the%20end%20coming%20closer%3F%20The%20simple%20answer%20to%20that%20question%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20his%20performances%20at%20the%20Slams%20would%20be%20%E2%80%98yes'.%20But%2C%20having%20said%20that%2C%20one%20must%20remember%20that%20his%20number-one%20priority%20will%20be%20to%20recalibrate%20his%20game%20such%20that%20he%20can%20continue%20to%20compete%20and%20aim%20to%20win.%20Will%20he%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20for%20Djokovic%2C%20winning%20matches%20and%20titles%20is%20an%20extremely%20emotional%20process%2C%20a%20continuous%20validation%20of%20sorts%20that%20he%20well%20and%20truly%20belongs%20at%20the%20highest%20level.%20He%20has%20had%20to%2C%20through%20his%20career%2C%20silence%20many%20a%20critic.%20Every%20success%20at%20the%20highest%20level%20is%20a%20reminder%20of%20just%20how%20far%20he%20has%20come.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThere%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20he%20is%20a%20very%2C%20very%20special%20player.%20And%20he%20knows%20it%20too.%20He%20couldn't%20garner%20a%20fan%20base%20as%20large%20and%20as%20loyal%20as%20the%20ones%20that%20Federer%20and%20Nadal%20have%2C%20but%20he%20has%20found%20a%20way%20to%20turn%20that%20into%20motivation%2C%20using%20that%20as%20rocket%20fuel%20to%20stoke%20the%20fire%20that%20burns%20within%20him.%20Imagine%20being%20the%20world%20number%20one%20at%2037%3B%20no%20other%20male%20player%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20sport%20has%20been%20older%20while%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20rankings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPicking%20His%20Battles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Djokovic%20has%20clearly%20realised%20that%20the%20time%20has%20come%20to%20really%20pick%20and%20choose%20his%20tournaments%2C%20with%20slams%20as%20the%20big%20priority.%20It%20wasn't%20really%20a%20surprise%20to%20see%20him%20withdraw%20from%20the%20Paris%20Masters%2C%20where%20he%20was%20the%20defending%20champion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20still%20hasn't%20made%20the%20cut%20for%20the%20season-ending%20ATP%20Finals%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing%20this%20essay.%20Four%20of%20the%20eight%20slots%20have%20already%20been%20filled.%20Currently%2C%20Djokovic%20is%20sixth%20in%20the%20race%2C%20behind%20Taylor%20Fritz.%20Don't%20be%20too%20surprised%20if%20he%20doesn't%20get%20a%20ticket%20for%20Turin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20he%20will%20still%20be%20hungry.%20Such%20hunger%20is%20never%20satiated.%20It%20all%20boils%20down%20to%20where%20Novak%20Djokovic%20is%E2%80%94physically%2C%20mentally%2C%20emotionally%20and%20psychologically.%20He%20might%20well%20be%20standing%20at%20the%20biggest%20crossroads%20of%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20a%20former%20sports%20editor%20and%20primetime%20sports%20news%20anchor.%20He%20is%20currently%20a%20columnist%2C%20features%20writer%20and%20stage%20actor)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730290500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fampj4lt_novak_625x300_30_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fto-play-or-not-to-play-novak-djokovic-stands-at-a-crossroads-6908201%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20Djokovic%20slowing%20down%3F%20Can%20he%20feel%20the%20end%20coming%20closer%3F%20The%20simple%20answer%20to%20that%20question%20vis--vis%20his%20performances%20at%20the%20Slams%20would%20be%20yes.%20But%20one%20must%20remember%20that%20his%20number-one%20priority%20will%20be%20to%20recalibrate%20his%20game.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fto-play-or-not-to-play-novak-djokovic-stands-at-a-crossroads-6908201%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Mindset%20of%20spoilt%20prince'%3A%20BJP%20slams%20Cong%20after%20ECI%20rejects%20Haryana%20poll%20claims%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%